<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="295" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,968,1211]" pageId="28" pageNumber="295">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,968,994]" pageId="28" pageNumber="295">Distribution</emphasis>
: Known from Pacific coast of Northern America from South-Eastern 
<collectingRegion box="[1089,1167,968,994]" country="United States of America" name="Alaska" pageId="28" pageNumber="295">Alaska</collectingRegion>
to southern British Columbia in depth range of 
<quantity box="[433,518,1004,1031]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.9" metricValueMax="7.1" metricValueMin="0.7" pageId="28" pageNumber="295" unit="m" value="39.0" valueMax="71.0" valueMin="7.0">7–71 m</quantity>
on mud (
<bibRefCitation author="Hendrycks, E. A. &amp; Bousfield, E. L." box="[624,960,1004,1030]" pageId="28" pageNumber="295" pagination="45 - 113" refId="ref19107" refString="Hendrycks, E. A. &amp; Bousfield, E. L. (2004) The amphipod family Pleustidae (mainly subfamilies Mesopleustinae, Neopleustinae, Pleusymtinae and Stenopleustinae) from the Pacific coast of North America: systematics and distributional ecology. Amphipacifica, 3 (4), 45 - 113." type="journal article" year="2004">Hendrycks &amp; Bousfield 2004</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="295" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,968,1211]" pageId="28" pageNumber="295">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1040,1066]" pageId="28" pageNumber="295">Remarks</emphasis>
. Perhaps this species includes individuals from the north-eastern coast of North America (Grand Manan Island, Fundy Bay), which were identified by Holmes (1904) as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Kroyer, 1845)" baseAuthorityName="Kroyer" baseAuthorityYear="1845" box="[978,1432,1076,1103]" class="Malacostraca" family="Epimeriidae" genus="Paramphithoe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="28" pageNumber="295" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulchella">
<emphasis box="[978,1251,1076,1102]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="295">Paramphithoe pulchella</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kroyer, H." box="[1268,1424,1076,1103]" pageId="28" pageNumber="295" pagination="10" refId="ref19281" refString="Kroyer, H. (1845) Crustaces. In: Gaimard, P. (Ed.), Atlas de Zoologie. Voyages de la Commission scientifique de Nord en Scandinavie, en Laponie, au Spitzberg et aux Feroe pendant les Annees 1838, 1839, et 1840 sur la Corvette La Recherche, Commandee par M. Fabvre. Arthus Bertrand, Paris, pl. 10." type="book chapter" year="1845">Krøyer, 1845</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Exemplars from Fundy Bay are close in morphology to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hendrycks &amp; Bousfield" authorityYear="2004" box="[784,961,1112,1138]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pleustidae" genus="Neopleustes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="28" pageNumber="295" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="columbianus">
<emphasis box="[784,961,1112,1138]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="295">N. columbianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(especially in dorsal carination) (Holmes, 1904: pl. 8, fig. 1), but differ from the typical description of 
<bibRefCitation author="Kroyer, H." box="[824,985,1148,1175]" pageId="28" pageNumber="295" pagination="10" refId="ref19281" refString="Kroyer, H. (1845) Crustaces. In: Gaimard, P. (Ed.), Atlas de Zoologie. Voyages de la Commission scientifique de Nord en Scandinavie, en Laponie, au Spitzberg et aux Feroe pendant les Annees 1838, 1839, et 1840 sur la Corvette La Recherche, Commandee par M. Fabvre. Arthus Bertrand, Paris, pl. 10." type="book chapter" year="1845">Krøyer (1845)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Sars, G. O." box="[1039,1168,1148,1175]" pageId="28" pageNumber="295" refId="ref19694" refString="Sars, G. O. (1895) An account of the Crustacea of Norway, with short descriptions and figures of all the species. Parts 31 / 32 Appendix. A. Cammermeyer, Christiania and Copenhagen, pp. 673 - 711, Supplement pls. 1 - 8. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 1164" type="book" year="1895">Sars (1895)</bibRefCitation>
(
<figureCitation box="[1184,1267,1148,1174]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1513,1537]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,446,1490]" captionTargetId="figure-113@29.[151,1436,446,1490]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 18. Neopleustes aff. columbianus Hendrycks &amp; Bousfield, 2004 (=Paramphithoe pulchella (Krøyer, 1845) (?)) from the coast of Grand Manan Island, Fundy Bay (after Holmes 1904)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4775613" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4775613/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="295">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
). However, the lack of own description in Holmes (1904) does not allow us to precisely state this.
</paragraph>
